chest.Descriptions: Lie on the floor with either two dumbbells or two kettlebells on your hand. Press one arm at a time, while the other hand is stationary. Lower your pressing hand until either your elbow or triceps touches the floor. Press the weight back up and repeat with the other hand.

Lie flat on the bench, Lift the bar out of the rack straight above your chest with arms locked. Come down slowly until the bar touches the middle of your chest. After a brief pause push the bar straight up while breathing out.

Lie flat on the bench, Lift the bar out of the rack straight above your chest with arms locked. Come down slowly until the bar is about 1 inch from your neck. After a brief pause push the bar straight up while breathing out.

Sit down either on the floor or a bench, have your back straight and chest up. Place your hand on the back of your hand. Have someone or partner place their hands on your elbows and pull your elbows back until there's a stretch in your chest. Hold it for a few secoonds and bring your elbows in. Relax and repeat.

Attach resistence bands on two ends of the barbell. Lie flat on the bench, Lift the bar out of the rack straight above your chest with arms locked. Come down slowly until the bar touches the middle of your chest. After a brief pause push the bar straight up while breathing out.
